{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Hair"], "type": "title", "extent": [59, 68], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [68, 104], "text": ["Simulates the look of hair."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [104, 147], "text": ["This operator simulates the look of hair."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [147, 567], "text": ["The most important parameter is ", {"text": ["Hair Width"], "type": "ui"}, " (", {"text": ["width"], "type": "code"}, "), which controls the\nwidth of the hair. You can create a float Point attribute\ncalled ", {"text": ["width"], "type": "code"}, " using the ", {"text": ["AttribCreate SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribcreate", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribcreate"}, " in the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ", and assign it to the curves representing the hairs to be shaded. This allows you to control the width of the hair based on the length, or some\nother attribute, of each hair."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [567, 661], "text": ["The roundness of each hair is determined by the value of the ", {"text": ["Bump Scale"], "type": "ui"}, "\n(", {"text": ["scale"], "type": "code"}, ") input."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [661, 1167], "text": ["If the Normal Vector (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") and S Texture Coordinate (", {"text": ["s"], "type": "code"}, ") inputs are not\nconnected, the global variables by the same names will be used instead.\nTypically, you will use the ", {"text": ["Shading Layer"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter as the input for ", {"text": ["s"], "type": "code"}, " and\nyou will not touch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement\nto the hair surface using an operator such as ", {"text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, ". If you need to access the global variables directly, they are available from the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1176, 1200], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1200, 1223], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/skin", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/skin"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1167, 1176], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates the look of hair."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "hair", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/hair"}, "title": ["Hair"]}